# 2. こはねの課題

Kohane: (I have to become strong enough to blast a hole in the moment RAD WEEKEND became a legend...?)
Kohane: (The moment when... He's talking about...)
Ken: Let me get one thing clear first.
Ken: If you're all able to accomplish the tasks I give you and achieve your true potential, then you should have no problem putting on an event just as good as RAD WEEKEND.
Ken: No... Not should. I know that you will.
Ken: However...
Ken: “Just as good” isn't good enough. Your goal is to surpass it, right?
Kohane: Oh...
Ken: “This is just like RAD WEEKEND.” “It's that night all over again.”
Ken: For better or worse, as long as you're trying to surpass that night, you won't be able to avoid being compared with it. That just comes with the territory.
Ken: Which brings me to your task.
Ken: You'll need to find a way to break open the door that takes you all from being “just as good” to actually surpassing it.
Kohane: The door...?
Ken: That's right.
Ken: You've all experienced it a number of times already.
Ken: When things really matter, she absolutely explodes.
An: Oh...
An: Yeah, I know what you mean.
An: Kohane...has this way of finding gears that we didn't imagine she had.
Akito: Yeah, she does.
Toya: Yes, Azusawa sometimes enters a state where she channels all of her energy into her singing. When she does, she's explosive.
Ken: Exactly. That's what you need to bet on.
Ken: She only has to reach that peak for a second. Actually, a second might be all you can manage.
Ken: She has to create that moment. A moment that drives the audience far wilder than we did that night.
Ken: Blast a hole in that moment. Then, they'll all know for sure.
Ken: They'll say, “This event isn't just an echo of RAD WEEKEND.”
Ken: They'll see it as a new legend unfolding before their eyes.
Ken: After that, the rest of you will have to propel yourselves forward using absolutely everything you have.
Ken: Her task is just to get the door moving. Whether or not you're able to push it wide open will depend on your collective resolve.
Ken: But knowing all of you...
Ken: I'm sure you'll succeed. I firmly believe that.
Kohane: (So, if I can do that for even a second...)
Kohane: (If I can get the door open just a crack, then we'll get our chance. We might actually be able to go beyond Nagi and her team's dream.)
Kohane: (But...)
Kohane: (That moment...)
Kohane: (No... I shouldn't be thinking about whether or not I can.)
Kohane: (I just have to do this.)
Kohane: (I have to succeed no matter what!)
Ken: Obviously, accomplishing this task is going to be the furthest thing from easy.
Ken: Which is why you need to become stronger. It'll all be for naught if you achieve that moment but don't have the strength to actually succeed.
Kohane: The strength to actually succeed...
Ken: That's right. Which is why...
Ken: You'll be receiving some special coaching.
